# Practice Stack - Components

## UI Components
- [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui) - shadcn/ui base components (buttons, inputs, etc.)
- [components/navbar/](mdc:components/navbar) - Navigation and header components
- [components/AppInputFields/](mdc:components/AppInputFields) - Custom form input fields

## Custom Components
- [app/_components/](mdc:app/_components) - App-specific components like headers and shared layouts

## UI Design Principles
- Use a clean, modern UI with proper spacing and visual hierarchy
- Create visually engaging interfaces with Lucide React icons
- Consistently use shadcn theme colors through CSS variables (`--primary`, `--foreground`, etc.)
- Follow a mobile-first approach with responsive designs
- Implement subtle animations and transitions for a polished feel

## Common Component Usage
Examples of component usage patterns:

```tsx
// Button component with variants
<Button variant="outline">Click Me</Button>
<Button asChild>
  <Link href="/signup">Get Started Free</Link>
</Button>

// Card component with content
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription>Card description goes here</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <p>Main content goes here</p>
  </CardContent>
  <CardFooter>
    <Button>Action</Button>
  </CardFooter>
</Card>

// Custom input field
<InputField
  label="Email"
  placeholder="Enter your email"
  type="email"
  required
/>
```